112 070h |                         | CBB_ROW_LOOP:
112 070h |                         | 
112 070h |                         |     ; When combining bounding boxes, several cases may occur:
112 070h |                         |     ;
112 070h |                         |     ;   1.  Both this NP and the one downstream have NULL coordinate pairs.  In
112 070h |                         |     ;       this case, the coordinate pairs should remain NULL
112 070h |                         |     ;
112 070h |                         |     ;   2.  This NP has NULL data, but the upstream NP has valid data.  In this
112 070h |                         |     ;       case, the incoming coordinate pairs should overwrite the local ones.
112 070h |                         |     ;
112 070h |                         |     ;   3.  This NP has valid data, but the upstream NP does not.  In this case,
112 070h |                         |     ;       the coordinate pairs should not be modified.
112 070h |                         |     ;
112 070h |                         |     ;   4.  Both this NP and the downstream NP have valid coordinate data.  Each
112 070h |                         |     ;       coordinate pair must be compared and the more inclusive one saved.
112 070h |                         |     ;
112 070h |                         |     ; NOTE: When an NP is asleep, it will not write any data to memory or 
112 070h |                         |     ;       registers, so any data that needs to be access from a sleeping
112 070h |                         |     ;       NP through the NSWE data bus must already be loaded in r0..r3.
112 070h |                         | 
112 070h |                         |     ; Copy incoming coordinates locally to prevent NPs from receiving 
112 070h |                         |     ; out-of-sync data.
112 070h |                         | 
